=1> A few hours ago I just had my first attempt at the Kromrif leggings quest, and it was a disaster. I'm level 44 and I had a level 44 warrior and 50 paladin with me at the time. They came a bit into the wurm cave with me, I went ahead and turned in the item, reinvised, and head out with the broodmother. Both of her guards saw through invis and attacked me, so while my friends were helping me out the broodmother got way ahead, triggered the spawns and by the time we reached the fort, fergul had just got away and despawned.<br>
Luckily a friend had gem and blood wolf harness with him, so I'm ready to do the quest again. This time I just want to plan it a little better, any tips? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualuaeia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aluaeia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Just got my shots!</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/02 11:34:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> Have the melees wait at the fort, and when you're doing the turnin, check if the Guardians see invis before you do the hand in to the broodmother.<br>
<br>
Great leggings though, I used mine for 20 levels, heh, 34-54 until I got some brown chitin leggings that I wore for about a week until I got Elysian.  I did the quest with a level 53 druid friend of mine back at 34. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39316">Aluaeia Evangelion</a>
<br>Level 55 Fier`dal Preserver of Tunare
<br>Tarew Marr
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utweezlelorespinner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tweezle Lorespinner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/02 1:41:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> With SOW you can blow right by the Guardian Wurms and to the battle point, well ahead of the Broodmother. Wurms will give up the chase and bail once you are a distance away.<br>
<br>
Invis to BM's room, ALONE, do the turn-in while your group is assembled on the ridge leading to the EW zone, re-invis and run to meet them. The rest is scripted, assuming no yutz player(s) butt in. BM goes to the fort and attacks, Fergul depops, repops, and runs toward zone. Take him down halfway between the fort and the zone line.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufernwick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fernwick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/02 1:57:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> You can also bind by the fort and gate there after you trigger the broodmother.<br>
<br>
Fernwick Wolfson<br>
54th. Wanderer on Zeb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilencerga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silencer GA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/02 2:28:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the help.<br>
<br>
Another question, would it be possible for just me (44 druid) and my level 44 warrior friend to take him down by ourselves? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualuaeia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aluaeia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Just got my shots!</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#333399>(7/24/02 1:48:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> It'd be very close if it is.  Maybe if you agro kite him?  Not sure, only time's I've done/helped out with the fight it's been an overwhelming force type of thing.  <br>
<br>
When I did mine at 34 (heh), I had a 53 druid friend doing most of the fighting, but an epic (anonymous) shaman was there too, I know he epic'd it once, and poked it a few times, there were also a few bored melees there to poke for faction.<br>
<br>
Another time I think I was 42 or 43 doing faction/exp down in the luclin spire valley area, and someone started the quest, but they nearly died and couldn't finish the giant, so me and my group killed it for them.<br>
<br>
I did see one messed up version just a few days ago.  There were 2 Ferguls and none of the other guy (I think some jackass killed him when they found out someone was going to do the quest), and the broodmother never came near the fort until one of the Ferguls died and the other agro'd her.  It was strange. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39316">Aluaeia Evangelion</a>
<br>Level 55 Fier`dal Preserver of Tunare
<br>Tarew Marr
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uraldos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raldos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 11:26:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif leggings problems..</span><hr size=1> I had just completed this quest a few days ago,with a 49 druid and a 51 druid(me).I had my guildmate wait at the fort,while I went  and did the turn in to the Broodmother.Luckily,I was able to avoid all the wurms who could see invis and didn't draw any aggro.I then followed the broodmother out,and we jumped on fergul when he started to run.It was a tough fight for us,was hard to get snare to stick and we kept getting adds.Then my Guildmate went LD,but luckily fergul was almost dead so it wasn't to hard for me to finish him off.A very nice pair of pants. = ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rohkit>Rohkit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 4:48:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> To avoid adds, don't fight anywhere near the fort.  There's a good spot to kite Fergul near the Eastern Wastes zone.  It's to the south as you come out of the ravine and onto the ridge.  There's a pretty good sized area there that nothing paths in--a couple of giants/wolves will ghost through the area, but they're not really there; they stop at the ridgeline.  Stick over by the stone cliff wall, and you can kite to your heart's content.  Solo'd him at 48 this way--took a heckuva long time, he snared fine but wouldn't stay rooted very often.  Just stay invis until Fergul runs over that way and then attack him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urezinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rezinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Finally Housebroken!</span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#333399>(8/10/02 6:06:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I did this quest last week. Fergul didn't spawn when the broodmother got to the fort, so I sat there till she walked away and camped unhappily. I logged back in 20 minutes later and tracked a pair of ferguls and the other guy. Apparently the quest is still bugged, but I managed to get my pants. Very easy kill at 57.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showPrevMessage?topicID=5392.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showNextMessage?topicID=5392.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5392.topic&index=8><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=5392.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a F